{"pageProps":{"wordpressPage":{"id":226,"date":"2011-02-02T18:51:25","date_gmt":"2011-02-02T18:51:25","guid":{"rendered":"http://admin.pascalegirardin.art/?post_type=project&#038;p=226"},"modified":"2020-02-02T18:53:39","modified_gmt":"2020-02-02T18:53:39","slug":"buffed","status":"publish","type":"project","link":"https://admin.pascalegirardin.art/en/project/buffed/","title":{"rendered":"Buffed"},"excerpt":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"featured_media":111,"menu_order":0,"template":"","categories":[21,32,36,28,40],"polylang_current_lang":"en_CA","polylang_translations":[{"locale":"fr_CA","id":170}],"acf":{"size":"9","options_size":{"size":"9"},"align":"right","options_align":{"align":"right"},"subtitle":"Art souterrain","place":"World Trade Centre — Collective project — Pascale Girardin, Sterling Downey, Stephany Hildebrand and Wolfe Girardin","dates":"Février 2011","flexible_content":[{"acf_fc_layout":"text","text_content":"<p><em>Buffed</em> is a video installation projected on a mural of ceramic tiles whose irregular surface bears the traces of a struggle for its ownership. Its title is inspired by the term &#8220;buffing&#8221; commonly used by graffiti writers to describe the act of erasing, repainting or cleaning a graffiti or tag.</p>\n<p><em>Buffed</em> is in continuity with the projects yo sa va, <em>Intramuros</em>, <em>T OU</em> and <em>E Space</em>, which, through the medium of clay, studies vernacular modes of communication such as tag, text messaging, graffiti and urban art. In this short stop-motion film photographed by Stephany Hildebrand, Pascale Girardin takes on the role of an owner who tries to smooth the surfaces of her clay slabs, which have been damaged by graffiti artists. The video editing, carried out by Wolfe Girardin, highlights the power struggles between taggers and the owners of &#8220;tagged&#8221; buildings. While shooting the video, the particular characteristics of raw clay (such as fragility and sensitivity to pressure) were exploited in the process of creating marked, erased, damaged and subsequently restored slabs. Once fired and glazed in white, these tiles were used as a projection screen where the textures of their damaged surfaces remind us of the struggle for the possession of the wall. The juxtaposition of these two mediums brings to mind the notions of private property, gentrification and the institutionalization of art.</p>\n"},{"acf_fc_layout":"slider","images":[{"ID":114,"id":114,"title":"","filename":"Art_Souterrain_2011_Pascale_Girardin_4.jpg","filesize":55260,"url":"https://admin.pascalegirardin.art/app/uploads/2020/01/Art_Souterrain_2011_Pascale_Girardin_4.jpg","link":"https://admin.pascalegirardin.art/art_souterrain_2011_pascale_girardin_4/","alt":"","author":"1","description":"","caption":"","name":"art_souterrain_2011_pascale_girardin_4","status":"inherit","uploaded_to":0,"date":"2020-01-24 17:24:18","modified":"2020-01-26 21:30:12","menu_order":0,"mime_type":"image/jpeg","type":"image","subtype":"jpeg","icon":"https://admin.pascalegirardin.art/wp/wp-includes/images/media/default.png","width":500,"height":752,"sizes":{"thumbnail":"https://admin.pascalegirardin.art/app/uploads/2020/01/Art_Souterrain_2011_Pascale_Girardin_4-150x150.jpg","thumbnail-width":150,"thumbnail-height":150,"medium":"https://admin.pascalegirardin.art/app/uploads/2020/01/Art_Souterrain_2011_Pascale_Girardin_4-199x300.jpg","medium-width":199,"medium-height":300,"medium_large":"https://admin.pascalegirardin.art/app/uploads/2020/01/Art_Souterrain_2011_Pascale_Girardin_4.jpg","medium_large-width":500,"medium_large-height":752,"large":"https://admin.pascalegirardin.art/app/uploads/2020/01/Art_Souterrain_2011_Pascale_Girardin_4.jpg","large-width":500,"large-height":752,"1536x1536":"https://admin.pascalegirardin.art/app/uploads/2020/01/Art_Souterrain_2011_Pascale_Girardin_4.jpg","1536x1536-width":500,"1536x1536-height":752,"2048x2048":"https://admin.pascalegirardin.art/app/uploads/2020/01/Art_Souterrain_